{"article_id":"jbQPCJtMj8DIqavj","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"News on climate in the time of coronavirus","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Subscribe today","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Over the pandemic-filled last four months , one thing ' s become clear :","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Face masks can slow the spread of coronavirus","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"and help to flatten the curve .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The only issue ?","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Mask-wearing is starting to look like a giant collective action problem","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"- and many Americans are refusing to cooperate .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"For months , scientists and doctors waffled about the usefulness of masks .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"The Centers for Disease Control , or CDC , repeatedly told Americans not to buy or wear them","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"if they had no COVID-19 symptoms ;","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"in March , Anthony Fauci , one of the top White House advisors on the pandemic , told 60 Minutes","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that \" there ' s no reason","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"to be walking around with a mask . \"","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"But that messaging began to change","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"as new research emerged on masks ' efficacy ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and as countries with widespread mask use","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"- like Japan and South Korea -","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"appeared to squash the outbreak more quickly .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"In early April , the CDC reversed their recommendation ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"encouraging \" cloth face coverings \" as a voluntary health measure .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Earlier this month , the World Health Organization did the same ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"advising the general public to wear \" non-medical masks \"","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"wherever there is widespread transmission of the virus .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Always free , always fresh","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"The Beacon","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Other choices","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"Ask your climate scientist","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"if is right for you .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"See our privacy policy","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"According to a growing consensus , the coronavirus travels in droplets","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"spewed from peoples ' mouths","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"when they talk , cough , or breathe .","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"And the latest research indicates","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"while homemade masks don ' t protect the wearer much from virus-laden particles coming in ,","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"they do keep those droplets from spilling out .","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"( Medical-grade masks like N95s , on the other hand , do both . )","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"\" If you ' re wearing a mask ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"you ' re mainly doing it","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"to protect everybody else around you , \"","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"said Jay Van Bavel , associate professor of psychology and neural science at New York University .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"We would be better off","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"if everyone wore masks ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"but there ' s a small cost to each person","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"that wears them :","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"fogged-up glasses , irritated skin , or just the annoyance","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"of putting it on","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"and taking off .","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"That means there ' s an incentive","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"to \" free-ride \"","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"-","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"if everyone else wears a mask ,","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"their caution keeps you safe","depth":15},{"id":54,"text":"and spares you the trouble","depth":16},{"id":55,"text":"of having to wear one yourself .","depth":16},{"id":56,"text":"But","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"the more people free-ride ,","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"the more everyone is at risk .","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"In psychology , this type of scenario is known as a collective action problem , or social dilemma .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"These problems have plagued society for decades ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"particularly when it comes to the environment .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"The ecologist Garrett Hardin famously wrote about the \" tragedy of the commons , \" or the dangers","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that result","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"when everyone tries to free-ride on one shared resource , like an open pasture or a lake full of fish .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Climate change , meanwhile , may be the most notorious collective action problem of all ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"since it requires the cooperation of every country on the planet .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"America has a patchy record with collective action .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"It may not be a coincidence that the United States is the only country in the world","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"that ' s trying to withdraw from the 2015 Paris Climate Agreement ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"which calls on nations to cooperate","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"to fight dangerous climate change ,","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"or that we have an uneven history","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"of vaccinating children .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"Americans ,","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"it seems ,","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"don ' t always like being told what to do ,","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"even if it ' s in the best interest of their communities .","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"Part of the problem is the deep partisan divisions in the U.S.","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"Republicans are more likely to be individualists ,","depth":16},{"id":80,"text":"valuing personal choice and freedoms ;","depth":16},{"id":81,"text":"Democrats are more likely to look at how communities will be affected as a whole .","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"These divisions have shown up during the pandemic , sometimes in unexpected ways .","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"According to an analysis by Peter Sharkey , professor of sociology at Princeton University ,","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"one of the strongest predictors of compliance with social distancing is belief in climate change","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"- those","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"who accept","depth":17},{"id":87,"text":"that climate change is happening ,","depth":18},{"id":88,"text":"and is human-caused ,","depth":18},{"id":89,"text":"are more likely to stay at home .","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"Similarly , an April poll by Morning Consult found","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"that climate skeptics are much less likely to wear masks than those","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"\" concerned \" about climate change .","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"People","depth":17},{"id":94,"text":"worried about one collective action problem","depth":18},{"id":95,"text":"( climate change )","depth":18},{"id":96,"text":"appear more likely to be worried about another","depth":16},{"id":97,"text":"( COVID-19 ) .","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"Van Bavel , the psychology professor , says","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"that polarization doesn ' t automatically mean","depth":17},{"id":100,"text":"that these problems can ' t be addressed .","depth":17},{"id":101,"text":"In many cases , social norms and sanctions","depth":18},{"id":102,"text":"( think public shaming )","depth":18},{"id":103,"text":"can encourage cooperation .","depth":17},{"id":104,"text":"For example , secondhand smoke is a collective action problem ,","depth":16},{"id":105,"text":"but one","depth":18},{"id":106,"text":"that has , at least to some extent , been \" solved \" :","depth":18},{"id":107,"text":"Nonpartisan norms and regulations control where and how individuals can smoke","depth":18},{"id":108,"text":"so that they don ' t create respiratory problems for others .","depth":18},{"id":109,"text":"Another way","depth":16},{"id":110,"text":"to encourage cooperation","depth":16},{"id":111,"text":"is through role-modeling .","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"\" If somebody","depth":18},{"id":113,"text":"you look to","depth":19},{"id":114,"text":"and respect and trust","depth":19},{"id":115,"text":"is wearing a mask ,","depth":17},{"id":116,"text":"lots of research suggests","depth":17},{"id":117,"text":"you ' re going to be more likely to wear one , \"","depth":17},{"id":118,"text":"Van Bavel said .","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"Unfortunately , though , that trend cuts both ways","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"-","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"elite figures can also undermine cooperation","depth":16},{"id":122,"text":"when they eschew social norms .","depth":16},{"id":123,"text":"That has been the case for many prominent Republican leaders during the crisis .","depth":15},{"id":124,"text":"President Trump , for example , has repeatedly refused to wear a mask in front of cameras ,","depth":17},{"id":125,"text":"even though reports say","depth":18},{"id":126,"text":"that he sometimes wears one in private ;","depth":18},{"id":127,"text":"in a rambling interview with the Wall Street Journal last week , he also claimed","depth":17},{"id":128,"text":"that Americans wear masks","depth":19},{"id":129,"text":"not to protect themselves ,","depth":19},{"id":130,"text":"but to signal disapproval of him .","depth":18},{"id":131,"text":"But","depth":15},{"id":132,"text":"as evidence accumulates in support of masks ,","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"some Republicans are changing their tune .","depth":16},{"id":134,"text":"In Texas , Governor Greg Abbott spent months refusing calls by mayors","depth":17},{"id":135,"text":"to allow mandates for mask-wearing in public spaces ,","depth":17},{"id":136,"text":"saying","depth":17},{"id":137,"text":"that it might infringe on personal liberties .","depth":17},{"id":138,"text":"But , in light of Texas ' skyrocketing coronavirus cases and a desire","depth":17},{"id":139,"text":"to keep businesses open ,","depth":17},{"id":140,"text":"he has reversed this position .","depth":16},{"id":141,"text":"Many other governors across the country have also recommended or mandated the use of masks .","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"Now , the U.S. seems to be moving into a new stage of the coronavirus pandemic :","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"Counties and states are focusing less on forced social cohesion through stay-at-home orders and more on individual assessments of risk .","depth":14},{"id":144,"text":"As stores and restaurants reopen ,","depth":15},{"id":145,"text":"people are encouraged to make decisions for themselves about how","depth":17},{"id":146,"text":"- and when -","depth":17},{"id":147,"text":"to leave their homes .","depth":16},{"id":148,"text":"But mask-wearing can ' t be boiled down to a personal decision","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"if we want to slow the spread of the coronavirus .","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"It ' s not the first collective action problem","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"to stymie the country ,","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"and unfortunately , it won ' t be the last .","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"According to Sharkey ,","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"the roots of Americans ' stubbornness on collective action go much deeper than COVID-19 .","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"It might take better role models , firmer regulations , and stronger social norms ,","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"but","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"to address the pandemic","depth":16},{"id":158,"text":"- and combat even larger issues , like climate change -","depth":16},{"id":159,"text":"Americans are going to have to figure out a way","depth":16},{"id":160,"text":"to put society ' s interests above their own .","depth":16}],"relations":[{"parent":321,"left":0,"right":320,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":320,"left":1,"right":319,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":319,"left":166,"right":318,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":166,"left":163,"right":165,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":2,"right":162,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":162,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":165,"left":5,"right":164,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":164,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":181,"right":317,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":181,"left":8,"right":180,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":180,"left":175,"right":179,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":170,"right":174,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":170,"left":167,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":11,"right":168,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":168,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":14,"right":173,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":15,"right":172,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":171,"right":18,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":176,"right":178,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":21,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":317,"left":182,"right":316,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":182,"left":24,"right":25,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":316,"left":185,"ri